# Sanskrit Karaoke — social-publisher credentials.
#
# Copy this file to ".env" (which is git-ignored) and fill in the platforms you want.
# `python tools/schedule_drops.py --live` auto-loads .env. A platform posts ONLY when ALL
# of its variables below are set — leave a platform's vars blank to skip it. Real shell
# environment variables take precedence over this file. NEVER commit the real .env.
#
# Full step-by-step is in docs/USE_CASES.md → "Appendix D — Publisher credentials".

# ─── TELEGRAM ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Easiest — no app review. Uploads the local dist/<id>_9x16.mp4 directly.
#   1. In Telegram, message @BotFather → /newbot → follow prompts → copy the token.
#   2. Create your channel, then add the bot as an ADMIN with "Post messages" rights.
#   3. CHANNEL_ID = @publicusername, or the numeric -100… id for a private channel
#      (forward a channel post to @userinfobot to read the numeric id).
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_CHANNEL_ID=

# ─── VK ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Posts to a community wall (video.save → upload → wall.post).
#   1. Create a "Standalone" app at https://dev.vk.com/ (Manage → Create app).
#   2. Get a token with the `video` + `wall` scopes — either a community token
#      (Community → Manage → API usage → Create token, tick Video + Wall) or an OAuth
#      implicit-flow token with scope=video,wall,offline (offline = long-lived).
#   3. OWNER_ID = the community wall id as a NEGATIVE number, e.g. -123456789
#      (find the numeric id via https://regvk.com/id/ or the group page source).
VK_ACCESS_TOKEN=
VK_OWNER_ID=

# ─── FACEBOOK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Posts to a Facebook Page's videos. Uploads the local file directly.
#   1. https://developers.facebook.com/ → Create App (type: Business).
#   2. In Graph API Explorer, select your Page and grant: pages_manage_posts,
#      pages_read_engagement, pages_show_list.
#   3. Exchange the short token for a LONG-LIVED Page token (Access Token Debugger →
#      "Extend Access Token", or /oauth/access_token?grant_type=fb_exchange_token).
#   4. PAGE_ID: your Page → About → "Page transparency" (or GET /me/accounts).
FB_PAGE_ID=
FB_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# ─── INSTAGRAM ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reels. NOTE: Instagram cannot take a local file — it fetches the video from a PUBLIC URL.
#   1. Convert the IG account to Business/Creator and link it to your Facebook Page.
#   2. Same Meta app as Facebook; request instagram_basic + instagram_content_publish
#      (live posting needs Meta App Review + business verification for these).
#   3. BUSINESS_ACCOUNT_ID: GET /{page-id}?fields=instagram_business_account
#   4. ACCESS_TOKEN: the long-lived token carrying the instagram_* permissions.
#   5. VIDEO_BASE_URL: a public base URL that serves dist/<id>_9x16.mp4
#      (e.g. https://samskrtam.ru/karaoke/video → the publisher requests
#       https://samskrtam.ru/karaoke/video/<id>_9x16.mp4). Ties into hosting the MP4s.
IG_BUSINESS_ACCOUNT_ID=
IG_ACCESS_TOKEN=
IG_VIDEO_BASE_URL=

# ─── WORDPRESS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uploads the video and creates a DRAFT post (you review before publishing).
#   1. BASE_URL = your site root, e.g. https://samskrtam.ru (no trailing slash).
#   2. WP Admin → Users → Profile (edit your user) → "Application Passwords":
#      type a name → "Add New Application Password" → copy the generated value.
#      (Requires WordPress 5.6+ served over HTTPS, with the REST API reachable.)
#   3. WP_USER = your WordPress login; WP_APP_PASSWORD = the generated password
#      (the spaces WordPress shows are optional — with or without works).
WP_BASE_URL=
WP_USER=
WP_APP_PASSWORD=
